intro: Trachymene anisocarpa var. anisocarpa, commonly known as the variable trachymene, is a herbaceous plant native to Australia. It belongs to the family Apiaceae, which includes carrots and parsley, and is characterized by its finely divided, fern-like leaves. The plant produces small, white to pale purple flowers arranged in umbels, typical of the family. It thrives in moist, well-drained soils and is often found in woodland or swampy areas. Due to its ornamental value and ecological importance, it is sometimes cultivated in gardens.
